entries.title: Mexican Ex-Lawman Took Money from Cartels He Pursued, Prosecutors Say
entries.description: Genaro García Luna is accused of helping traffickers move drugs to the United States. But his defense says he is being targeted by the men he helped to send to prison.

entries.title: $20 Million Worth of Looted Art Returns to Italy From the U.S.
entries.description: The authorities of the two countries have worked together to round up statues, vases and bronzes, some of which had appeared in American museums.

entries.title: Power Outage Sweeps Pakistan, Dropping Millions Into Darkness
entries.description: Blackouts are becoming increasingly common in Pakistan, where small failures can lead to cascading effects through the nation’s deteriorating power grid.

entries.title: For British Farmers, the Effects of Brexit Have Become Clearer
entries.description: In the years since Britain voted to quit the E.U., many Eastern Europeans have left the country, adding to a shortfall of about 330,000 workers. The food and farming sectors have been hit particularly hard.

entries.title: Zelensky Vows Action Against Corruption After a Minister Is Fired
entries.description: The Ukrainian leader said the dismissal should serve as notice to officials whose actions “violate the principle of justice.”

entries.title: In Moscow, a Quiet Antiwar Protest With Flowers and Plush Toys
entries.description: Amid Russia’s crackdown on resistance to the war in Ukraine, some have dared to lay bouquets and other offerings at a statue of a Ukrainian poet, protesting the recent Russian strike on civilians in Dnipro.

entries.title: In Egypt, Eggs Are Becoming a Luxury and Lenders Are Setting Terms
entries.description: After months of punishing inflation and a plummeting currency value, Egyptians are growing louder about an economic crisis. In exchange for a bailout, the I.M.F. is imposing stern conditions on the government.

entries.title: Poland Aims to Push Smaller Group of Nations to Send Tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: Germany said it would not fight Poland’s move to ship the German-made tanks, which Ukraine has said are essential to fighting off a Russian advance.

entries.title: Mass Shooting in California
entries.description: A gunman killed 10 people at a dance studio.

entries.title: A New Zealand Road Trip: Wine, Salmon and Stunning Views
entries.description: A road trip on the country’s South Island offered perfect wines, stunning views, intimate restaurants and the chance to make a pilgrimage to a salmon Shangri-La.

entries.title: China’s Mad Dash Into a Strategic Island Nation Breeds Resentment
entries.description: For years, Beijing has thrown its wealth and weight across the globe. But its experience in the Solomon Islands calls into question its approach to expanding its power.

entries.title: Gunman Dies of Self-inflicted Gunshot After Mass Shooting in Monterey Park
entries.description: The attack took place in a city just east of Los Angeles that earlier in the day had hosted a festival celebrating the eve of the Lunar New Year.
